User spotlight time! We love to learn and get to know all of you a little better to find out what drives you, your challenges and proudest moments! Each of you has the power to inspire others with your success story. üôå
_
This picture was taken by Insa, an adidas Running user from Vaterstetten, Germany! Here, she explains why it‚Äôs crucial to find variety in where you run and the importance of not overtraining!
_
Q. How did you first get started running?
A. I always loved to be active and used to be a track and field athlete as a teenager. I just feel so alive when I am outdoors, running and hitting the street. After moving to Berlin, I had some issues like finding a proper running route that was long and green enough and not interrupted by a forest of traffic lights!üö¶
_
Q. Was there ever a time you wanted to stop? What kept you going?
A. With the lack of variety in where I could run, I lost my passion for running for a while. I was also suffering from amenorrhea due to overtraining, which is really difficult for many female athletes! I decided I had to take a training break. I changed my nutrition and tried to put less stress on myself ‚Äì I missed running a lot, but it was really necessary for me. üèÉ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
_
Q. What has been your biggest achievement?
A. I‚Äôm happy to bounce back a couple of months after my recovery! I feel more mindful, but no less powerful as you can see! Finding some new running routes has really helped, and I‚Äôm proud to say I‚Äôve completed several half marathons in the past. Next year, I‚Äôm thinking about taking on the big marathon in Berlin! üòâ
